data.title: The Biggest Celebrity Wedding The Year You Were Born
data.meta_description: These are some of the most iconic celebrity and royal weddings from every year over the past century
data.text:
No one can forget Brad Pitt's wedding to Angelina Jolie, but remember when he and Jennifer Aniston tied the knot? We do. (After all, their nuptials toted a million dollar price tag.) Throughout the past century, the world has seen countless celebrities say I do—some more than once—in lavish, over-the-top weddings that have graced the pages of tabloids, and later, websites. And we've been keeping tab.

From Princess Diana and Prince Charles' iconic nuptials to Elizabeth Taylor's eight different wedding celebrations, these are some of the biggest celebrity weddings of the past 70+ years. Forward this to your bridesmaids (and your mom! and your grandma!), so everyone can see what famous twosome said I do the year they were born. (Cheers to all the babies being born this year as Meghan Markle and Prince Harry tie the knot!)

01 of 75

1945: Shirley Temple and John Agar

Actors John Agar and Shirley Temple tied the knot in 1945 against her mother's wishes, as Temple was only 17 at the time. The two met through a friend, who arranged for Agar to escort Temple to a Hollywood party. The former child star wore a gorgeous satin wedding dress when she married Agar in her family's home, although the two eventually split in 1949.

02 of 75

1946: Jimmy Carter and Rosalynn Smith

Former President Jimmy Carter married Rosalynn Smith just days after graduating from the United States Naval Academy, in Annapolis, Maryland in 1946. The two are still married to this day and share four children together: Jack, Chip, Jeff and Amy.

03 of 75

1947: Queen Elizabeth and Philip Mountbatten

Queen Elizabeth and Prince Philip celebrated their 70th wedding anniversary on November 20, 2017. The two met nearly a century ago, when Elizabeth, who was only 13 at the time, visited the Royal Navy College (where Philip was studying) with her family. Phillip eventually proposed after a monthlong vacation at Balmoral with her family, but her father insisted that the engagement be kept secret until her 21st birthday. The two tied the knot at Westminster Abbey in London as Princess Elizabeth and Lieutenant Philip Mountbatten, where Elizabeth wore a duchesse-satin long-sleeved wedding gown with floral embroidery and crystal and 10,000 pearl appliqués.

04 of 75

1948: Dick Van Dyke and Margie Willett

Actor Dick Van Dyke married Margie Willet just one month after the two started dating in 1948. The two were married for 36 years and had four children together, but eventually divorced in 1984.

05 of 75

1949: Rita Hayworth and Prince Aly Khan

Prince Aly Khan, the son of the Aga Khan, married Hollywood starlet Rita Hayworth on May 27, 1949 at Khan's Riviera Chateau de L'Horizon. The two had one daughter together, Yasmin, but divorced four years later in 1953.

06 of 75

1950: Elizabeth Taylor and Conrad Hilton

Elizabeth Taylor's first of eight weddings was to Conrad Hilton on May 13, 1950. Taylor, who was only 18 at the time, wore a Helen Rose gown, which sold at a London auction for $187,931 in 2013. The two split a year later.

07 of 75

1951: Frank Sinatra and Ava Gardner

Frank Sinatra and Ava Garnder tied the knot in 1951, but split six years later in 1957. This was Gardner's third marriage and Sinatra's second.

08 of 75

1952: Ronald Reagan and Nancy Davis

Actor and future President Ronald Reagan married his second wife, actress Nancy Davis, on May 4, 1952, at the Little Brown Church in the Valley in Los Angeles. The two remained married for the rest of their lives, working through his two-term presidency together and sharing two children, Ron and Patti.

09 of 75

1953: John F. Kennedy and Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis

Jacqueline Onassis and former President John F. Kennedy were married on September 12, 1953 in St. Mary’s Church in Newport, Rhode Island in what might have been the most iconic wedding of the century. The former first lady stunned in an Ann Lowe gown for the big day, which even received a blessing from the pope. The couple remained married until Kennedy's assassination in 1963.

10 of 75

1954: Marlyn Monroe and Joe DiMaggio

The baseball superstar and the iconic actress tied the knot on January 14, 1954. The two were married at San Francisco City Hall, where they were bombarded by reporters and fans after Monroe accidentally revealed her wedding details to a colleague. The two split in October 1954, only 274 days after the wedding.

11 of 75

1955: Gregory Peck and Veronique Passani

Actor Gregory Peck and his wife, arts patron and journalist Veronique Passani, wed on New Year's Day in 1956, the day after his divorce from his first marriage was finalized. The two had two children together and remained married until Peck's death in 2003.

12 of 75

1956: Prince Rainier of Monaco and Grace Kelly

American actress Grace Kelly and Prince Rainier III of Monaco married in an elaborate two-day wedding in April aboard the SS Constitution on the French Riviera. Kelly's dress, which was designed by MGM costume designer Helen Rose, remains a dress design inspiration to this day. The royal couple stayed married until Kelly's death in 1982.

13 of 75

1957: Elizabeth Taylor and Michael Todd

Elizabeth Taylor's third marriage was to film producer Michael Todd, which took place in Mexico in 1957. The two had a daughter together shortly after, but Todd died just one year later in a plane crash.

14 of 75

1958: Robert Redford and Lola Van Wagenen

All The President's Men actor Robert Redford married environmental activist Lola Van Wagenen on September 12, 1958, in Las Vegas, Nevada. The two later split in 1985.

15 of 75

1959: Elizabeth Taylor and Eddie Fisher

A year after the death of her third husband, Michael Todd, Elizabeth Taylor met actor Eddie Fisher. At the time, he was married to Taylor's friend Debbie Reynolds, but left her to be with Taylor. The two divorced in 1964.

16 of 75

1960: Sandra Dee and Bobby Darin

Actress Sandra Dee and singer Bobby Darin ("Mack the Knife") married on December 1, 1960 in Camden, New Jersey. The two met while filming the rom-com Come September, in which they both co-starred. The couple divorced in 1967.

17 of 75

1961: Ginger Rogers and William Marshall

The musical movie star married director and producer William Marshall in 1961. It was the fifth and final marriage for the starlet, who later divorced Marshall 10 years later in 1971, following the collapse of their joint film production company.

18 of 75

1962: John Lennon and Cynthia Powell

Beatles legend John Lennon married his former classmate, Cynthia Powell, in 1962, but only remained married for four years. Powell filed for divorce in 1966 when Lennon left her for his second wife, Yoko Ono.

19 of 75

1963: Barbra Streisand and Elliott Gould

Elliott Gould and Barbara Streisand met when she auditioned for a musical he was starring in. The two married in 1963 and had one son together, but eventually split in 1971.

20 of 75

1964: Elizabeth Taylor and Richard Burton

Elizabeth Taylor and Richard Burton were married twice. The two first tied the knot in 1964 and remained married for 10 years until their split in 1974. They later remarried in 1975, but divorced again just one year later.

21 of 75

1965: Ringo Starr and Maureen Cox

Beatles drummer Ringo Starr married Maureen Cox in 1965. Beatles manager, Brian Epstein, served as best man, and bandmate George Harrison was a witness. The couple shared three children together, later divorcing in 1975.

22 of 75

1966: Frank Sinatra and Mia Farrow

Actress Mia Farrow married Frank Sinatra when she was 21 and he was 50. The two tied the knot in Las Vegas in 1966, but Sinatra filed for divorce just two years later.

23 of 75

1967: Elvis Presley and Priscilla Presley

Priscilla Wagner met rock legend Elvis Presley in 1959 when she was only 14 years old. They married on May 1, 1967 at the Aladdin Hotel in Las Vegas and had one child, Lisa Marie, together. The two split in 1972.

24 of 75

1968: Johnny Cash and June Carter Cash

Singers June Carter and Johnny Cash got engaged in 1968, when Cash popped the question during a live performance at the London Ice House in Ontario. The two married later that year and remained together until Cash's death in 2003.

25 of 75

1969: John Lennon and Yoko Ono

John Lennon was still married to his first wife, Cynthia, when he met Yoko Ono in 1966. Three years later, after leaving his first wife, the two tied the knot in 1969 in a quick, 10-minute ceremony in a British Consulate office. The two remained married until Lennon's death in 1980.

26 of 75

1970: Stevie Wonder and Syreeta Wright

Singer-songwriters Stevie Wonder and Syreeta Wright married in September 1970. The two wrote a handful of songs together before their divorce 18 months later in 1972.

27 of 75

1971: Mick Jagger and Bianca Perez Morena de Macias

Rolling Stone lead singer Mick Jagger married Bianca Pérez-Mora Macias in 1971 at the Chapel of St. Anne in Saint-Tropez, southern France, where Bianca donned her iconic bridal suit. The rock couple later divorced in 1978.

28 of 75

1972: James Taylor and Carly Simon

Carly Simon married fellow singer-songwriter James Taylor on November 3, 1972 and had two children together. The two stayed together for over 10 years until their divorce in 1983.

29 of 75

1973: Farrah Fawcett and Lee Majors

Actress and It-girl Farrah Fawcett married Lee Majors at the Hotel Bel-Air on July 28, 1973 in Los Angeles, California. The two remained married until their divorce in 1982.

30 of 75

1974: Faye Dunaway and Peter Wolf

Actress Faye Dunaway and musician Peter Wolf tied the knot at the Beverly Hills Municipal court in California in 1974. The Bonnie and Clyde actress and her husband stayed married until 1979.

31 of 75

1975: Greg Allman and Cher

Pop icon Cher and Allman Brothers Band musician Gregg Allman's relationship was fast and furious. The two met in early 1975, shortly after Cher's split from former husband Sonny Bono, and married later that year on June 30. Nine days later, Cher filed for divorce citing his drug and alcohol addictions as the cause of the split.

32 of 75

1976: Elizabeth Taylor and John Warner

Elizabeth Taylor's sixth marriage was to Republican politician John Warner. The two married on December 4, 1976, after Taylor had worked on his campaign with him. Their marriage only lasted a few years, and the two divorced in November 1982.

33 of 75

1977: Donald and Ivana Trump

We hate to say it, but this one was a biggie. Donald Trump married his first model wife, Ivana Zelníčková, in an over-the-top ceremony on April 7, 1977. The New York socialites had three children you might recognize: Ivanka, Eric, and Donald Jr. The two split in 1991.

34 of 75

1978: Meryl Streep and Don Gummer

Meryl Streep and husband Don Gummer have been going strong since their wedding in September 1978. The two have four children together, and continue to inspire us all with their commitment.

35 of 75

1979: Rod Stewart & Alana Hamilton

Actress and model Alana Hamilton married British rockstar Rod Stewart on April 6, 1979 at the L'Eermitage Restaurant in Beverly Hills, California. The two had two children together, but divorced in 1984.

36 of 75

1980: Karen Carpenter and Thomas Burris

Karen Carpenter of The Carpenters and real estate developer Thomas Burris wed at the Beverly Hills Hotel in August of 1980. The bride performed a new song, "Because We Are in Love," at the wedding that was later released in 1981. However, the marriage didn't last long and the couple divorced in 1982.

37 of 75

1981: Lady Diana Spencer and Prince Charles

Prince Charles and Lady Diana's televised wedding was the definition of iconic. The royal wedding took place on July 29, at Saint Paul's Cathedral in London. Diana's stunning gown was made of ivory silk taffeta and antique lace that once belonged to Queen Mary, and was hand-embroidered with mother-of-pearl sequins and 10,000 pearls. Despite the flawless nuptials, the two split in 1996, just a year before her tragic death.

38 of 75

1982: Ozzy and Sharon Osbourne

Black Sabbath musician Ozzy Osbourne and Sharon Arden were married on July 4, 1982 and had three children—and a reality show!—together. The two recently renewed their wedding vows for their 35th anniversary.

39 of 75

1983: Carrie Fisher and Paul Simon

Star Wars actress Carrie Fisher and singer Paul Simon tied the knot in August 1983, but divorced a year later due to issues with drug and alcohol abuse. Though they never remarried, the two dated on and off before Fisher's second marriage to Bryan Lourd.

40 of 75

1984: Janet Jackson and James DeBarge

Janet Jackson and R&B singer James DeBarge eloped in 1984, but the two annulled their marriage one year later in 1985. This was the first of three marriages for Jackson.

41 of 75

1985: Madonna and Sean Penn

The pop icon and actor Sean Penn tied the knot on August 16, 1985, Madonna's birthday. The singer filed for divorce in 1989, and it was said Penn's angry outbursts were the cause of their split.

42 of 75

1986: Arnold Schwarzenegger and Maria Shriver

The Terminator actor and journalist Maria Shriver first met at a charity tennis tournament being held at her mother's home in 1977, and tied the knot nine years later on April 26, 1986, in Hyannis, Massachusetts. The two have four children together, but divorced just last year.

43 of 75

1987: Lenny Kravitz and Lisa Bonet

Singer and musician Lenny Kravitz eloped with actress Lisa Bonet in Las Vegas in 1987, on Bonet’s 20th birthday. The two divorced in 1993, but share a daughter together named Zoë (you may have heard of her). Bonnet recently revealed that she is now married to her longtime love, Game of Thrones actor Jason Momoa.

44 of 75

1988: Tom Hanks and Rita Wilson

The Forrest Gump star and his wife's marriage has withstood the test of time—the two will celebrate their 30th anniversary in April. Hanks and Wilson (we wonder if her last name is a coincidence...) tied the knot on April 30, 1988.

45 of 75

1989: David Hasselhoff and Pamela Bach

Actor David Hasselhoff married his second wife, Pamela Bach, in December 1989 after meeting on the set of a Knight Rider episode. The couple had two daughters together, but filed for divorce in 2006 citing "irreconcilable differences."

46 of 75

1990: Nicole Kidman and Tom Cruise

Nicole Kidman and Tom Cruise first met in November 1989, while filming Days of Thunder. The two married one year later on Christmas Eve 1990 in Telluride, Colorado. The acting legends adopted two children together, but split in 2001. Kidman married her second husband, Keith Urban, five years later in 2006.

47 of 75

1991: John Travolta and Kelly Preston

The Grease actor and his wife, actress Kelly Preston, first met in 1987 while filming The Experts. The two tied the knot on September 5, 1991 in a wedding ceremony at the Hotel de Crillon in Paris. The two had a second ceremony later under the Church of Scientology.

48 of 75

1992: David Bowie and Iman

Late rockstar David Bowie and model Iman married on April 24, 1992, in a small civil ceremony in Switzerland. The adorable couple remained married until Bowie's death in 2016 and had one daughter together, Alexandria.

49 of 75

1993: Mariah Carey and Tommy Mottola

Mariah Carey married her former producer Tommy Mottola at St. Patrick's Cathedral in New York on June 5, 1993 in an over-the-top $500,000 affair inspired by Princess Diana and Prince Charles's wedding. (The bride even wore a $25,000 Princess Diana-inspired Vera Wang gown!) Some of their A-list guests included Barbra Streisand, Michael Bolton, Bruce Springsteen, Dick Clark, and Ozzy Osbourne.

50 of 75

1994: Michael Jackson and Lisa Marie Presley

Music icon Michael Jackson married Lisa Marie Presley in a secret wedding ceremony in the Dominican Republic in 1994. The two first met while Presley was on tour with her father, Elvis, when she was just a child. The two divorced two years later in 1996.

51 of 75

1995: Tommy Lee and Pamela Anderson

Mötley Crüe musician Tommy Lee and Pamela Anderson eloped in Cancun, Mexico in 1995, just days after they met. The couple stayed together until 2008, and share two sons together, Brandon and Dylan.

52 of 75

1996: Prince and Mayte Garcia

Late musician Prince first met Mayte Garcia backstage in Germany after he saw a tape of her dancing. After four years of dating, the two married on February 14, 1996. The two had one child together, a son, who died shortly after his birth due to a genetic disorder. The couple divorced in 2000.

53 of 75

1997: Matthew Broderick and Sarah Jessica Parker

Step aside, Mr. Big. Sex and the City's Sarah Jessica Parker and Ferris Bueller's Day Off actor Matthew Broderick tied the knot in the most Carrie Bradshaw-appropriate wedding: A civil ceremony in a historic synagogue on the Lower East Side of Manhattan, where Parker donned a chic black wedding dress for the occasion.

54 of 75

1998: Cindy Crawford and Rande Gerber

After separating from actor Richard Gere in 1995, supermodel Cindy Crawford married former model Rande Gerber on May 29, 1998. The family continued their modeling dynasty, giving birth to two children, Kaia and Presley, both of whom are now models.

55 of 75

1999: David and Victoria Beckham

Spice Girls singer Victoria Beckham and soccer superstar David Beckham tied the knot in a very Posh $800,000 affair at Ireland's Luttrellstown Castle on July 4, 1999. The two are coming up on 20 years together, and share four children: Brooklyn, Romeo James, Cruz, and Harper Seven.

56 of 75

2000: Brad Pitt and Jennifer Aniston

Who can forget this wedding? Jennifer Aniston and Brad Pitt tied the knot in a $1 million affair on July 29, 2000 in Malibu. Naturally, all of Aniston's Friends co-stars were in attendance. (Do you think Ross was jealous?) Sadly, the couple split in 2005.

57 of 75

2001: Halle Berry and Eric Benét

Actress Halle Berry married her second husband, singer-songwriter Eric Benét, on January 24, 2001. The couple separated in October 2003 and finalized their divorce two years later.

58 of 75

2002: Jessica Simpson and Nick Lachey

Actress and singer Jessica Simpson married former 98 Degrees singer Nick Lachey on October 26, 2002. Their nuptials inspired a reality TV show, Newlyweds: Nick and Jessica. The two split in 2006.

59 of 75

2003: Gwyneth Paltrow and Chris Martin

Chris Martin, the lead singer of Coldplay, and actress Gwyneth Paltrow married in 2003 and only officially divorced in 2016—just one year before Paltrow became engaged to Glee producer Brad Falchuk. At the time of her divorce, the actress shared in a statement on her blog, Goop, "We have come to the conclusion that while we love each other very much we will remain separate. We are, however, and always will be a family, and in many ways we are closer than we have ever been."

60 of 75

2004: Britney Spears and Kevin Federline

The pop legend and the former backup dancer married in a surprise wedding on September 18, 2004. The two invited guests to what was assumed to be an engagement party, where they arrived to find Spears in a $26,000 strapless silk gown. The two were married for three years before a dramatic divorce and custody battle.

61 of 75

2005: Ben Affleck and Jennifer Garner

Two months after the couple broke the news of their engagement, actors Ben Affleck and Jennifer Garner tied the knot in a quiet ceremony in Turks and Caicos on June 29, 2005—and announced shortly thereafter that they were expecting. The two separated in 2015, but didn't file for divorce until 2017. The two share three children together, Violet, 12, Seraphina, 9, and Sameuel, 6.

62 of 75

2006: Tom Cruise and Katie Holmes

On November 18, 2006, the Top Gun actor and the Dawson's Creek actress tied the knot in Bracciano, Italy. The two had their ceremony in a 15th-century Odescalchi Castle, and the bride wore two different dresses, both designed by Giorgio Armani. The $3 million affair was filled with A-list guests, including Brooke Shields, Will and Jada Pinkett Smith, fellow Scientologists John Travolta and Kelly Preston, David and Victoria Beckham, Marc Anthony and Jennifer Lopez, and a handful of other VIPs. Sadly, TomKat spilt five years later in 2012.

63 of 75

2007: Eva Longoria and Tony Parker

Desperate Housewives star Eva Longoria and NBA player Tony Parker married in a civil ceremony in Paris, France on July 6, 2007. The two split in 2011, amongst rumors that the basketball player had been unfaithful. However, the two sited "irreconcilable differences" as the reason for their split. Longoria has since married José Antonio Bastón and is now pregnant with her first child.

64 of 75

2008: Beyoncé and Jay-Z

Modern music legends Beyoncé and Jay-Z tied the knot on April 4, 2008 inside Jay’s New York City penthouse. The two kept their lavish wedding relatively small, inviting only 40 guests to the big day. The couple now share three children together, Blue Ivy, 6, and twins Rumi and Sir, 1.

65 of 75

2009: Gisele Bündchen and Tom Brady

NFL star Tom Brady and supermodel Gisele Bündchen married on February 26, 2009 at the Santa Monica Catholic Church outside of Los Angeles, California in a private 20-person ceremony, before jetting off to Bündchen's Costa Rica property for a second celebration. "We planned [the wedding] in like 10 days, and it was perfect," Brady told GQ. "We went back to the house and I barbecued aged New York strips. We had champagne, a cake, some ice cream. It was a great night."

66 of 75

2010: Katy Perry and Russell Brand

Pop singer Katy Perry and actor Russell Brand had a whirlwind romance that just barely lasted a year. The two wed in a small ceremony in India in October 2010, only for Brand to file for a divorce—which he informed Perry of through a text message—just 14 months later.

67 of 75

2011: Kate Middleton and Prince William

Prince William and Kate Middleton's wedding was one of the biggest and most exciting of the decade. On April 29, 2011, the now-Duke and Duchess of Cambridge tied the knot in Westminster Abbey in London and the celebration was made a public holiday in the United Kingdom. The two share two children together, Prince George, 4, and Princess Charlotte, 2, and are expecting a third child this year.

68 of 75

2012: Justin Timberlake and Jessica Biel

Singer Justin Timberlake and actress Jessica Biel said their I do's in Puglia, Italy on October 19, 2012. The bride wore a unique petal-pink Giambattista Valli Haute Couture gown for the occasion, while the groom stunned in a Tom Ford tux. The couple, who never fails to make us jealous of their affection for one another, will celebrate their sixth anniversary this year.

69 of 75

2013: John Legend and Chrissy Teigen

Model Chrissy Teigen and Grammy-winning singer John Legend met in 2007 on the set of Legend's music video "Stereo." Four years later, Legend popped the question on Christmas 2011 in the Maldives. The couple wed in 2013 at the stunning Villa Pizzo in Lake Como, Italy, where Legend serenaded his bride with his song "All of Me." The two share daughter Luna and are expecting a son in summer 2018.

72 of 75

2015: Justin Theroux and Jennifer Aniston

Actors Justin Theroux and Jennifer Aniston wed on August 5, 2015, in the backyard of their Bel Air home. The two had quite the guest list, which was made up of 70 guests and included Howard Stern, Orlando Bloom, Friends stars Lisa Kudrow and Courteney Cox, Ellen Degeneres, Chelsea Handler, Emily Blunt and John Krasinski, and Sia. Sadly, the two split less than two years later, in mid-February 2018.

73 of 75

2016: Michael Phelps and Nicole Johnson

The Olympic swimmer and his wife wed in not one, not two, but three ceremonies in 2016. The couple first celebrated in an intimate, five-person backyard ceremony at their home in Tempe, Arizona in June. Shortly after, the newlyweds jetted off to Cabo San Lucas, Mexico for a larger celebration with 50 of their closest family and friends on October 29, 2016. Finally, the two celebrated their last set of nuptials with a big, black-tie New Year's Eve bash at the historic Arizona Biltmore, A Waldorf Astoria Resort. Needless to say, Michael Phelps definitely brought home the gold in celebrity weddings that year.

74 of 75

2017: Serena Williams and Alexis Ohanion

Tennis superstar Serena Williams officially tied the knot with Reddit cofounder Alexis Ohanian on November 16, 2017 at the Contemporary Art Center of New Orleans. The two were joined by dozens of A-list guests, including Beyoncé, Kim Kardashian, Eva Longoria, Kelly Rowland, and Anna Wintour. The bride wore two stunning dresses for the affair—a ball gown designed by Sarah Burton from Alexander McQueen for the ceremony and a short, feathered dress by Versace for the reception. Needless to say, the ceremony was fit for a princess—which perfectly fit the Beauty and the Beast theme of their wedding.

75 of 75

2018: Meghan Markle and Prince Harry

Though Prince Harry and Meghan Markle have yet to tie the knot, their date is set for May 19, 2018, and the event will undoubtedly be the biggest wedding of the year. From Meghan's wedding dress predictions to who has made the coveted guest list, you can get every last detail about the upcoming royal wedding here!
